# 🧪 JavaScript Practice Tasks

## 1️⃣ Synchronous Execution

### Task 1: Log Three Messages

```javascript
// Print three messages in order
console.log("Start");
console.log("Middle");
console.log("End");
```

---

### Task 2: Function Calling Another Function

```javascript
// Second function
function secondFunction() {
    console.log("Inside second function");
}

// First function
function firstFunction() {
    console.log("First function started");
    secondFunction(); // Call second function
    console.log("First function finished");
}

// Run the function
firstFunction();
```

---

### Task 3: Sequential Calculations

```javascript
// Store numbers
let num1 = 20;
let num2 = 5;

// Calculate sum
let sum = num1 + num2;
console.log("Sum:", sum);

// Calculate product
let product = num1 * num2;
console.log("Product:", product);
```

---

### Task 4: Function Depending on Another Function

```javascript
// Return square of a number
function square(number) {
    return number * number;
}

// Use the returned value
function calculateResult(number) {
    let result = square(number);
    console.log("Square is:", result);
}

// Execute
calculateResult(6);
```
